    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-11-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-11-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="405" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d405">
                <head>No. 1118.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Scott</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Carácas</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-11-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 30, 1887</date>.
                            (Received December 13.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 204.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge the receipt of
                        your No. 136, in relation to the closing of the ports of Venezuela against
                        Curaçao, and to state that I will avail myself of the first opportunity to
                        make known to the Venezuelan Government, through Dr. Urbaneja, minister of
                        exterior relations, your views on this subject, as expressed in your No.
                        126, and dated Washington, September 22, 1887, thus carrying out the
                        instructions embraced in your No. 136.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Charles L. Scott.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
